com.tractrac.clientmodule

Class CompetitorClass

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.tractrac.clientmodule.details.Attachments
      • com.tractrac.clientmodule.details.IdBase
        • com.tractrac.clientmodule.details.IdBaseNamed
          • com.tractrac.clientmodule.CompetitorClass

  • public class CompetitorClass
extends IdBaseNamed
    Encapsulates data related to a Competitor Class in a TracTrac Event.

    All Competitors of an Event are typically divided into groups or classes. An instance of a Competitor Class can be used to represent data related to such a group/class.

    An instance of this class has a unique id and a name. Custom data may be attached to each Competitor Class instance.

    Use Event.addCompetitorClass(java.util.UUID, java.lang.String) to create a new Competitor Class.

    Version:
    2.0
    Author:
    TracTrac
    See Also:
    Event, Competitor
